Tom Young wrote:

>He's speaking about the "flapper" in the AFM.  In my experience, >putting the pedal to the floor on a Volkswagen when starting only >helps when the mixture is too rich since it introduces much more air >into the engine which helps burn the excess fuel.

Ahh yes, I had the wrong flapper. Isn't the 'flooring it' a visious cycle since introducing the air to burn the fuel asks the computer for more gas to burn with the air anyway?

>The cold start system is completely independent of the ECU.  If the
>thermo-time switch senses that it's cold enough it allows current to >flow to the cold start valve when the key is in the "start" >position, opening up the valve and giving the engine that >extra "squirt" of fuel it needs on startup.

Sneaky thermo time switch, then does the cold start valve not ground on the manifold (therefore two prong connection to supply a ground?)

